com.gwtplatform.mvp.client.proxy
Interface TabContentProxy<P extends Presenter<?,?>>

Type Parameters:
P - The type of the Presenter associated with this proxy.
All Superinterfaces:
HasHandlers, Proxy<P>, ProxyRaw
All Known Subinterfaces:
NonLeafTabContentProxy<P>, TabContentProxyPlace<P>
All Known Implementing Classes:
NonLeafTabContentProxyImpl, TabContentProxyPlaceImpl
public interface TabContentProxy<P extends Presenter<?,?>>
extends Proxy<P>

The interface for the Proxy of a Presenter that can be displayed within a TabContainerPresenter's main area. You should not use this proxy directly. If the presenter is associated to a name token use TabContentProxyPlace instead. If the presenter is not a leaf, so it is not associated with a name token, use NonLeafTabContentProxy instead.

Author:
Philippe Beaudoin

getTargetHistoryToken

String getTargetHistoryToken()
Gets the history token that should be accessed when the tab is clicked. In the fairly typical scenario where a tab directly contains a place, this should return the name token of that place. In the case of tabs that contain non-leaf presenters (for example, other tabs), this should return the name token of a leaf-level presenter. See NonLeafTabContentProxy.

Returns:
The history token.

changeTab

void changeTab(TabData tabData)
Changes the data associated with this tab. This will automatically cause the displayed tab to change, provided the TabContainerPresenter containing this tab defines a ChangeTab field and passes it to the parent constructor.
